    {
      "step_id": "7f85f0d2",
      "step_index": 8,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "hERG blockers typically bind in the **inner cavity** accessible from the cytosolic side, stabilized by:\n- **Hydrophobic/\u03c0 interactions** with aromatic residues (e.g., Y652/F656 in many discussions of hERG binding),\n- Often an additional **electrostatic anchor** from a **protonated amine**.",
      "tool_name": null,
      "tool_input": null,
      "tool_output": null,
      "timestamp": "2026-02-26T19:53:47.553010+00:00"
    },
    {
