      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "For this molecule:\n- It can provide **\u03c0 surfaces** (fused ring + phenyl) to engage aromatic residues.\n- But it **cannot provide a strong cationic anchor**, and the **carboxylate** increases polarity and may reduce residence in the cavity.\n- The shape is relatively **rigid/planar**, which can sometimes fit, but rigidity alone doesn\u2019t compensate for missing cationic interaction in many potent blockers.",
